Zablon Kerima: Detection of new strains an indicator of good science
To say that the Covid-19 pandemic has subjected humanity to untold suffering is an understatement.
Being a novel virus, scientists from diverse backgrounds pulled out all the stops to understand its biology, a process that unravelled vital information about the virus, enabling scientists to embark on efforts to develop safe and effective vaccines.



